## Flight Summary

| # | Village | Body | Key Note | Tannin | Price |
|---|---------|------|----------|--------|-------|
| 1 | Marsannay | Light | Dried cherry | Gossamer | €22 |
| 2 | Gevrey-Chambertin | Full | Smoked meat | Grippy | €38 |
| 3 | Chambolle-Musigny | Med-light | Rose petal | Silky | €45 |
| 4 | Vosne-Romanee | Full | Spice box | Plush | €65 |
| 5 | Nuits-Saint-Georges | Med-full | Truffle | Firm | €42 |

**The lesson this flight teaches:** Pinot Noir is the most terroir-transparent grape in the world. Same producer, same vintage, same winemaking — and yet five completely different wines. The vine did not change. The rock beneath it did.
